						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the same shrine.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīrarājēndradēva: Year 17, Māśi = c. 1223-24 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>A portion of this inscription is lost. It records the gift of one hundred <hi rend="italic">achchu</hi> (coins) to provide for food-offerings (probably to the deity Avināśi Āḷuḍaiyār), by a person (name lost). It mentions a certain <hi rend="italic">brāhmaṇa</hi> named Śivallan.</p>						

